# Chapter 1: The Boy and the Dog in the Tower

## Story

### The Tower on the Hill

![A tall stone tower standing on a green hill under a blue sky, with Hebrew text "מגדל" (tower) and "גבעה" (hill) visible in the scene](tall-stone-tower-hill-blue-sky-hebrew-text-migdal-givah)

בְּרֹאשׁ הַגִּבְעָה עָמַד מִגְדָּל גָּדוֹל. הַמִּגְדָּל עָמַד שָׁם יָמִים רַבִּים. עָמַד הַמִּגְדָּל וְחָכָה.

### The Boy Named Rider

![A young boy with dark hair wearing a red uniform standing in front of the tower, with Hebrew text "ילד" (boy) and "ריידר" (Rider) visible](young-boy-dark-hair-red-uniform-tower-background-hebrew-text-yeled-rider)

בַּמִּגְדָּל יָשַׁב יֶלֶד. שֵׁם הַיֶּלֶד רַיְדֶר. יָשַׁב רַיְדֶר בַּמִּגְדָּל וְחָשַׁב. חָשַׁב הַיֶּלֶד עַל כְּלָבִים. אָהַב רַיְדֶר כְּלָבִים מְאֹד.

### Marshall the Puppy Arrives

![A small red and white Dalmatian puppy with a firefighter helmet approaching the tower, with Hebrew text "גור כלבים" (puppy) and "מרשל" (Marshall) visible](small-red-white-dalmatian-puppy-firefighter-helmet-tower-hebrew-text-gur-klavim-marshal)

יוֹם אֶחָד בָּא גּוּר כְּלָבִים אֶל הַמִּגְדָּל. שֵׁם הַגּוּר מַרְשֶׁל. בָּא מַרְשֶׁל וְרָץ. רָץ הַגּוּר מָהֵר מְאֹד.

### First Meeting

![The boy Rider and the puppy Marshall meeting each other in front of the tower, both looking happy, with Hebrew text "פגש" (met) visible](boy-rider-puppy-marshall-meeting-tower-both-happy-hebrew-text-pagash)

רָאָה רַיְדֶר אֶת מַרְשֶׁל. רָאָה מַרְשֶׁל אֶת רַיְדֶר. פָּגַשׁ הַיֶּלֶד אֶת הַגּוּר. פָּגַשׁ הַגּוּר אֶת הַיֶּלֶד. שָׂמַח רַיְדֶר מְאֹד. שָׂמַח גַּם מַרְשֶׁל.

### The Training Begins

![Rider teaching Marshall basic commands, with Marshall sitting and paying attention, training equipment visible, Hebrew text "למד" (learned) and "צוה" (commanded) shown](rider-teaching-marshall-basic-commands-sitting-training-equipment-hebrew-text-lamad-tzivah)

צִוָּה רַיְדֶר לְמַרְשֶׁל. צִוָּה הַיֶּלֶד וְהַגּוּר שָׁמַע. שָׁמַע מַרְשֶׁל וְלָמַד. לָמַד הַכֶּלֶב מַהֵר. לָמַד מַרְשֶׁל לִשְׁמֹעַ אֶל רַיְדֶר.

### Living Together

![Rider and Marshall eating together at a table inside the tower, with bowls of food, showing their daily life together, Hebrew text "אכל" (ate) and "שתה" (drank) visible](rider-marshall-eating-together-table-tower-bowls-food-daily-life-hebrew-text-achal-shatah)

יָשַׁב רַיְדֶר עִם מַרְשֶׁל בַּמִּגְדָּל. יָשְׁבוּ יַחְדָּו וְאָכְלוּ. אָכַל הַיֶּלֶד וְאָכַל הַכֶּלֶב. שָׁתָה רַיְדֶר וְשָׁתָה מַרְשֶׁל. אָהַב כָּל אֶחָד אֶת חֲבֵרוֹ.

## Vocabulary

### Nouns
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| מִגְדָּל | tower |
| גִּבְעָה | hill |
| יֶלֶד | boy |
| גּוּר | puppy |
| כֶּלֶב | dog |
| כְּלָבִים | dogs |
| חָבֵר | friend |
| יוֹם | day |
| שֵׁם | name |

### Proper Names
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| רַיְדֶר | Rider |
| מַרְשֶׁל | Marshall |

### Adjectives
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| גָּדוֹל | big |
| אֶחָד | one |
| רַבִּים | many |
| מָהֵר | fast |

### Adverbs
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| מְאֹד | very |
